<inglise> Council Regulation (EEC) No 1201/90 of 7 May 1990 on measures to increase the consumption of citrus fruit </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 1201/90 tsitrusviljade tarbimise suurendamise meetmete kohta 7. mai 1990 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 43 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 43, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the consumption of citrus fruit within the Community is stagnating; whereas, moreover, surpluses of citrus fruit are withdrawn from the market each year; whereas there are possibilities of increasing quantities consumed, in particular by bringing production closer into line with consumer taste; whereas, moreover, fruit and vegetables are healthy products the consumption of which should be encouraged as part of a health policy; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: tsitrusviljade tarbimise kasv on &uuml;henduses peatunud; lisaks sellele k&otilde;rvaldatakse igal aastal turult tsitrusviljade &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;gid; tarbitavaid koguseid on v&otilde;imalik suurendada eelk&otilde;ige sellega, et tootmine viiakse rohkem vastavusse tarbijate eelistustega; lisaks sellele on puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljad tervislikud tooted, mist&otilde;ttu tuleks nende tarbimist soodustada tervishoiupoliitika osana; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the producer organizations have an important role to play in the implementation of measures to achieve that development: </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuse arengu saavutamiseks vajalike meetmete rakendamisel on oluline osa tootjaorganisatsioonidel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas provision should be made for specific measures so that consumption may be encouraged by a Community financial contribution towards the measures implemented; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks n&auml;ha ette erimeetmed, et soodustada tarbimist rakendatavate meetmete suhtes antava &uuml;henduse rahalise toetuse abil; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the aim of the measures provided for is to achieve the objectives laid down in Article 39 of the Treaty; whereas provision should be made for a Community financial contribution towards the implementation of those measures from the Guarantee Section of the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund (EAGGF), </inglise>
<eesti> etten&auml;htud meetmete eesm&auml;rk on asutamislepingu artiklis 39 s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rkide saavutamine; k&otilde;nealuste meemete rakendamiseks tuleks n&auml;ha ette &uuml;henduse rahaline toetus Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi (EAGGF) tagatisrahastu kaudu, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The Community shall make a contribution of up to 60 % towards the financing of measures to encourage an increase in the consumption of fresh citrus fruit harvested in the Community, including research into varietal diversification, presented and conducted by representative groups involving various branches of activity in the sector. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendus osaleb kuni 60% ulatuses &uuml;henduses koristatud v&auml;rskete tsitrusviljade tarbimise suurendamist soodustavate meetmete rahastamises, sealhulgas sektori eri tegevusharusid esindavate t&uuml;&uuml;piliste r&uuml;hmade poolt esitatavate ja juhitavate sortide mitmekesistamist k&auml;sitlevate uuringute rahastamises. </eesti>
<inglise> The representative nature of the groups shall be evaluated on the basis of the aim pursued. </inglise>
<eesti> R&uuml;hmade t&uuml;&uuml;pilisust hinnatakse taotletava eesm&auml;rgi p&otilde;hjal. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The measures provided for in this Regulation must not relate to trade marks and must not refer to any Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed ei tohi olla seotud kaubam&auml;rkidega ning neis ei tohi viidata &uuml;helegi liikmesriigile. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> The contribution towards the financing of the measures provided for in this Regulation shall be deemed intervention intended to stabilize the agricultural markets within the meaning of Article 3 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 of the Council of 21 April 1970 on the financing of the common agricultural policy (4), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2048/88 (5). </inglise>
<eesti> Osalemist k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmete rahastamises k&auml;sitatakse sekkumisena, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on p&otilde;llumajandusturgude stabiliseerimine n&otilde;ukogu 21. aprilli 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 (&uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika rahastamise kohta, (4) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2048/88 (5)) artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 1 m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall be financed by the EAGGF Guarantee Section. </inglise>
<eesti> Meetmeid rahastab EAGGFi tagatisrahastu. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The measures provided for in this Regulation shall be defined and the detailed rules for the application of this Regulation shall be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 33 of Regulation (EEC) No 1035/72 of the Council of 18 May 1972 on the common organization of </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed m&auml;&auml;ratletakse ja k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamise &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad v&otilde;etakse vastu n&otilde;ukogu 18. mai 1972. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1035/72 (puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (6) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1193/90 (7)) artiklis 33 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub selle Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 7 May 1990. </inglise>
